              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5799885-aoibh-nn?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5799885-aoibh-nn?shelf=2012">2012</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5799885-aoibh-nn?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5799885-aoibh-nn?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer201722951" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3871927229748855035">An absolutely amazing novel! I found it very hard to put this novel down. This is one of those books, were you&apos;re desperate to get to the end, to find out the outcome, but at the same time, you don&apos;t want the novel to end. Heather Gudenkauf writes from the perspective of each character, and her descriptions of the violence and the fear that surround Calli and Ben are both breathtaking and heart-wrenching.</span>
  <span id="freeText3871927229748855035" style="display:none">An absolutely amazing novel! I found it very hard to put this novel down. This is one of those books, were you're desperate to get to the end, to find out the outcome, but at the same time, you don't want the novel to end. Heather Gudenkauf writes from the perspective of each character, and her descriptions of the violence and the fear that surround Calli and Ben are both breathtaking and heart-wrenching.</span>
