  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_147015771" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/147015771" />
    <a title="Carol" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3845138-carol"><img alt="Carol" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1438649960p2/3845138.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/147015771?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol" href="/user/show/3845138-carol">Carol</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer147015771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer389969868198937855">Well written and suspenseful. I enjoyed listening to an audio version of this novel, which was told through multiple voices with various points of view. It was as much about the complexities of living in an dysfunctional, alcoholic home as it was a mystery, although I did have to sit in the garage a few times in order to wrap up a segment of the CD. The author realistically depicts the &quot;elephant in the living room&quot; behavior within a family, in which the alcoholic member significantly impacts the</span>
  <span id="freeText389969868198937855" style="display:none">Well written and suspenseful. I enjoyed listening to an audio version of this novel, which was told through multiple voices with various points of view. It was as much about the complexities of living in an dysfunctional, alcoholic home as it was a mystery, although I did have to sit in the garage a few times in order to wrap up a segment of the CD. The author realistically depicts the "elephant in the living room" behavior within a family, in which the alcoholic member significantly impacts the remainder of the family...yet no one talks about it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="389969868198937855" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


